def quantile(self, q=0.5, axis=0, numeric_only=True, interpolation="linear"):
    """
    Return values at the given quantile over requested axis.

    (Parameters, See Also, and Examples remain unchanged)

    """
    # Validate the input percentile value
    self._check_percentile(q)

    # Retrieve the numeric data from the dataframe
    data = self._get_numeric_data() if numeric_only else self

    # Get the axis number
    axis_number = self._get_axis_number(axis)
    
    is_transposed = axis_number == 1

    if is_transposed:
        data = data.T

    # Calculate the quantile
    result = data.quantile(q=q, axis=axis_number, interpolation=interpolation)

    if is_transposed:
        result = result.T

    return result
